<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<alarm-config>

	<!-- 
		***************************************************************************************

	The configured alarms configured within this application .

	Each alarm configuration requires the following information .
	
	The transactionId identifies the context from which the alarm is Generated .
	
	The alarmAttribute identifies the measurable parameter with a name .
	
	The threshold indicates the point of violation for the above measurable . This can be negative or positive integer	
	-ve sign indicates the violation is a downfall 
	and
	+ve sign indicates the violation is a overflow
	
	The notificationInterval indicates the configured minimum time between two consecutive notifications generated by a particual
	event . The value is in seconds.
	
	The thresholdCount indicates how many violation occurances , should go for notification. 
	
	The thresholdInterval indicates the interval period the violation occurances should be cached in memory . 
	Once a notification is sent the memory is clearred to receive fresh data .
	
	The message can be a meaningul remark for this . This is not used anywhere .
	
	The notifiers indicates the ACTION to be called . A comma separated string of ACTION names
	LOGGER - a file logging action will be called
	MAIL   - a mail sending action will be called.			

	     	******************************************************************************************
	-->
	
